South Africa&rsquo;s new Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba would meet with the National Treasury executive committee on Friday as he prepared to take over control of the public purse, his office said. In a short statement, Gigaba&rsquo;s office said he was humbled by his appointment to serve the country and its people as finance minister. &ldquo;He has had discussions with his predecessor, Mr Pravin Gordhan, and they have agreed to a meeting soon,&rdquo; the statement said. &ldquo;The Minister-designate has met with the National Treasury Director-General and has therefore been briefed on pertinent and most urgent issues.&rdquo; Gigaba plans to address his first media briefing as Finance Minister on Saturday.